THE GAME
--------

  'TiltOtix' is a Workbench game where you have to move a coloured
bar from the upper left, to the lower right of the game board. The
game board is filled with 24 bars, including the coloured bar,
each occupying two spaces. An empty space is placed somewhere on
the game board.

  To move a bar, it must be beside the empty space. Clicking on
part of a bar that is next to the empty space will make the bar
rotate towards the empty space.

  One thing to keep in mind is that the 'bow tie' shaped bars can
rotate and can be placed in any position, even diagonally.
However, the coloured bar can only be placed horizontally or
vertically...

  When a portion of the coloured bar is placed on the small square
at the bottom right of the game board, the game is completed...

  Complete the game in the least amount of moves...

  Have fun!

